title: Qatar University's  Wendy Krausse  speaks about Egypt protests
description:
Subscribe to our channel http://bit.ly/AJSubscribe

Protesters have started to gather at Tahrir square after Friday prayers to protest about the lack of change since the military took over the country after Hosni Mubarak's ouster.

Al Jazeera speaks to Wanda Krause, a political strategy analysis in the Middle East with the Gulf Studies Programme at Qatar University in Doha.

She explains why she thinks protesters are frustrated at the pace of change, despite promises of reform.
